the bidding amounts are...

550
00:34:14,640 --> 00:34:16,790
- Two hundred thousand dollars.
- Fine.

551
00:34:16,880 --> 00:34:18,359
We have $200,000. Do I hear...

552
00:34:18,440 --> 00:34:20,875
Two hundred thousand and one dollar.

553
00:34:21,240 --> 00:34:22,240
(CROWD LAUGHING)

554
00:34:25,240 --> 00:34:27,038
Mr. Wayne.

555
00:34:27,520 --> 00:34:29,557
How about you let someone else
have some fun?

556
00:34:29,800 --> 00:34:33,634
Oh! Sure. No problem.
I'm sorry about that.

557
00:34:38,480 --> 00:34:40,630
- Three hundred thousand.
- AUCTIONEER: Very well,

558
00:34:40,800 --> 00:34:41,870
three hundred thou...

559
00:34:41,960 --> 00:34:43,997
Three hundred thousand dollars

560
00:34:44,080 --> 00:34:45,354
and one cent.

561
00:34:45,920 --> 00:34:47,274
(CROWD LAUGHING)

562
00:34:47,360 --> 00:34:49,317
Five hundred thousand.

563
00:34:50,880 --> 00:34:52,678
Now back off. You little brat.

564
00:34:52,920 --> 00:34:55,753
Wow, Ms. Kean.
That's a lot of money.

565
00:34:56,400 --> 00:34:57,799
For someone like you.

566
00:34:58,000 --> 00:34:59,991
Two million dollars!

567
00:35:00,240 --> 00:35:01,435
(ALL GASPING)

568
00:35:01,880 --> 00:35:02,880
BARBARA: Two...

569
00:35:02,960 --> 00:35:05,110
Sold to Mr. Bruce Wayne.

570
00:35:10,560 --> 00:35:11,914
(LAUGHS)

571
00:35:14,480 --> 00:35:16,357
Congratulations, Bruce.

572
00:35:16,760 --> 00:35:18,159
Thank you.

573
00:35:21,120 --> 00:35:23,634
(LAUGHING) I do love
seeing that woman lose.

574
00:35:24,120 --> 00:35:25,758
A little piece of friendly advice.

575
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:27,832
Barbara Kean does not give up easily.

576
00:35:27,920 --> 00:35:29,558
She'II be coming for that knife.

577
00:35:30,160 --> 00:35:32,913
I would just, uh, keep a close eye
on it if I were you.

578
00:35:37,680 --> 00:35:40,194
There's a new wrinkle, isn't it?

579
00:35:44,400 --> 00:35:46,357
What's green and red and goes
round and round?

580
00:35:47,040 --> 00:35:48,917
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

581
00:35:50,840 --> 00:35:52,797
S0me0ne's obsessed
with the color red.

582
00:35:54,560 --> 00:35:56,631
The answer obviously
isn't newspaper.

583
00:35:57,440 --> 00:35:58,510
You're stalling.

584
00:35:58,960 --> 00:36:00,598
(CHUCKLES) No.

585
00:36:02,200 --> 00:36:03,315
You don't know the answer.

586
00:36:03,400 --> 00:36:04,470
Of course I do.

587
00:36:04,760 --> 00:36:05,989
No. you don't. Ed!

588
00:36:08,880 --> 00:36:10,712
- (GASPS)
- Mmm-hmm.

589
00:36:11,200 --> 00:36:13,999
Your brilliant mind is as damaged
as the rest of your body.

590
00:36:16,000 --> 00:36:17,035
Actually.

591
00:36:17,960 --> 00:36:19,189
My body is feeling fine.

592
00:36:22,480 --> 00:36:24,232
Frog in a blender!

593
00:36:33,560 --> 00:36:35,039
(wum BLOWING)

594
00:36:39,200 --> 00:36:40,429
BRUCE: Selina?

595
00:36:43,480 --> 00:36:47,474
Why are you sitting
in the dark by yourself?

596
00:36:48,040 --> 00:36:49,314
I was expecting someone else.

597
00:36:49,400 --> 00:36:50,549
Like who?

598
00:36:50,640 --> 00:36:51,710
Doesn't matter.

599
00:36:51,800 --> 00:36:52,870
What are you doing here?

600
00:36:54,080 --> 00:36:56,515
I heard about Penguin's auction.

601
00:36:57,720 --> 00:36:59,677
So, Barbara sent you for the knife.

602
00:37:00,280 --> 00:37:02,794
Figured, what? Because we're friends
I'd just hand it over?

603
00:37:03,120 --> 00:37:04,235
Something like that.

604
00:37:05,280 --> 00:37:06,509
Why is it so important to her?

605
00:37:06,600 --> 00:37:07,749
How should I know?

606
00:37:07,840 --> 00:37:10,070
She was supposed
to get it for some client.

607
00:37:10,640 --> 00:37:12,392
Said he was a pretty dangerous guy.

608
00:37:13,600 --> 00:37:15,511
And that if you were smart.

609
00:37:15,640 --> 00:37:17,916
You'd hand it over
and save yourself the trouble.

610
00:37:18,840 --> 00:37:20,239
So, you're here to protect me.

611
00:37:20,320 --> 00:37:21,390
Is that it?

612
00:37:21,480 --> 00:37:23,630
The knife can't possibly mean
that much to you, Bruce.

613
00:37:23,760 --> 00:37:24,875
I don't know.

614
00:37:24,960 --> 00:37:27,873
Like you said, I spent $2 million on it.
I think I'II keep it.

615
00:37:28,320 --> 00:37:30,197
- Why are you acting like this?
- Me?

616
00:37:31,320 --> 00:37:33,834
What about you? Are you really
Barbara Kean's errand girl now?

617
00:37:33,920 --> 00:37:35,354
I'm her partner.

618
00:37:36,000 --> 00:37:38,674
But if I don't give
her this knife back,

619
00:37:38,880 --> 00:37:41,030
she won't ever see me <i>as</i> an equal.

620
00:37:44,400 --> 00:37:46,118
I'm asking you to do me a solid.

621
00:37:48,000 --> 00:37:49,354
I'm sorry, Selina.

622
00:37:50,000 --> 00:37:51,149
You should go.

623
00:38:17,360 --> 00:38:18,475
Morning, Harv.

624
00:38:19,160 --> 00:38:20,160
HARVEY: Jim, hey.

625
00:38:21,440 --> 00:38:24,558
This is Detective Harper. She just
transferred over from the three-five.

626
00:38:25,280 --> 00:38:27,000
- Jim Gordon.
- Nice to meet you, Detective.

627
00:38:27,040 --> 00:38:28,120
Heard a lot of good things.

628
00:38:28,240 --> 00:38:29,310
From who?

629
00:38:29,920 --> 00:38:31,560
It's good to have you in the fold.
Harper.

630
00:38:31,640 --> 00:38:32,640
Thanks.

631
00:38:36,880 --> 00:38:38,075
ALVAREZ: Gordon.

632
00:38:38,440 --> 00:38:39,714
You got a visitor.

633
00:38:41,240 --> 00:38:42,435
HARVEY: Hot damn.

634
00:38:43,320 --> 00:38:44,515
Fox in the hen house.

635
00:38:45,120 --> 00:38:46,190
No offense, Harper.

636
00:38:46,920 --> 00:38:48,035
HARPER: None taken.

637
00:38:49,720 --> 00:38:51,200
But you got the wrong idiom, Captain.

638
00:38:51,240 --> 00:38:53,038
- No, I don't.
- Be right back.

639
00:38:57,200 --> 00:38:58,235
Soña?

640
00:38:59,000 --> 00:39:00,035
What are you doing here?

641
00:39:00,720 --> 00:39:01,869
I came to help you.

642
00:39:02,600 --> 00:39:03,670
Yeah? How is that?

643
00:39:04,480 --> 00:39:07,996
Penguin. Oh, I know you didn't directly
ask me, but...

644
00:39:08,360 --> 00:39:10,670
I find men tend to have trouble
seeing the simple solution

645
00:39:10,760 --> 00:39:12,433
even when it's presented to them.

646
00:39:12,520 --> 00:39:13,874
You shouldn't
have come back here.

647
00:39:15,160 --> 00:39:17,197
Oh, Jim.

648
00:39:18,080 --> 00:39:20,993
(EXHALES) I don't need your permission.
Or my father's.

649
00:39:21,760 --> 00:39:23,194
I'm a Falcone.

650
00:39:23,360 --> 00:39:24,919
This city is my binhright.

651
00:39:25,280 --> 00:39:26,759
My father might not think I'm ready.

652
00:39:26,840 --> 00:39:28,592
But I am.

653
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:30,195
Is that so?

654
00:39:31,960 --> 00:39:34,918
What do you think I've been doing
down south. the past 10 years?

655
00:39:39,760 --> 00:39:41,433
You knew you were coming back

656
00:39:41,520 --> 00:39:43,272
from the moment
I left your father's house.

657
00:39:44,080 --> 00:39:46,071
Everything that's happened was what?

658
00:39:46,560 --> 00:39:47,880
You sizing me up?

659
00:39:47,960 --> 00:39:50,554
No. Not everything.

660
00:39:53,280 --> 00:39:55,590
But I had to get to know you
if we're gonna work together.

661
00:39:55,680 --> 00:39:56,875
We're not.

662
00:39:56,960 --> 00:39:59,998
Don't be sore, Jim.
You came looking for a gangster.

663
00:40:00,080 --> 00:40:01,593
That's exactly what you found.

664
00:40:03,960 --> 00:40:06,076
We can do great things together,
you and I.

665
00:40:07,200 --> 00:40:08,554
I'Il be in touch.

666
00:40:15,400 --> 00:40:16,470
You?

667
00:40:17,280 --> 00:40:19,078
You're the one who stole from me?

668
00:40:20,080 --> 00:40:21,400
MYRTLE: Some good it did.

669
00:40:21,840 --> 00:40:23,433
The ice broke his brain.

670
00:40:23,600 --> 00:40:24,795
What are you talking about?

671
00:40:25,680 --> 00:40:27,751
What's green and red and goes
round and round?

672
00:40:29,080 --> 00:40:30,150
Frog in a blender.

673
00:40:30,600 --> 00:40:32,876
Exactly.
Ed couldn't even get that.

674
00:40:34,640 --> 00:40:38,474
It does seem unlike Ed
to keep this rube alive.

675
00:40:39,720 --> 00:40:41,711
Sound the word. I want him found.

676
00:40:43,040 --> 00:40:44,110
And her?

677
00:40:45,080 --> 00:40:47,549
A lot of people have been trying to
steal from me lately.

678
00:40:47,640 --> 00:40:49,233
An example needs to be made.

679
00:40:50,600 --> 00:40:52,432
Have fun, Victor.

680
00:41:01,520 --> 00:41:03,716
- Love your dress.
